Scripts (NSE)

--> Run Default Scripts
nmap -sC <target>
Runs a set of safe, useful default scripts.
Use when: General info gathering alongside a scan.

--> Vulnerability Scan
nmap --script vuln <target>
Checks for known vulnerabilities.
Use when: Security audit on your own systems.

--> HTTP Scripts
nmap --script http-* <target>
Runs all HTTP-related scripts.
Use when: Testing a web server.

--> SSL/TLS Check
nmap --script ssl-enum-ciphers -p 443 <target>
Checks SSL/TLS configuration and cipher strength.
Use when: Verifying HTTPS security on your server.

--> Find Available Scripts
ls /usr/share/nmap/scripts/

--> Get Help on a Script
nmap --script-help <script-name>
